                                    be a giant relief for his family who currently must feed him lying
                                    down. Martin can also be taught to grasp and hold things. Sounds
                                    simple? Such things would bring relief to Martin and his family.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                    I vouch that this child has a genuine need and is deserving of
                                    help. I do not know the family and cannot guarantee that they
                                    would use the money correctly once they received it. They
                                    obviously care about this child because of the time and energy
                                    they invest in making him comfortable, but they might have other
                                    pressures they consider a priority. A giver ought to make arrangements
                                    to ensure that the money is spent correctly. Lázaro Martinez
                                    ought to be able to help with that, and I vouch for Lázaro with
                                    all my heart and soul.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
